				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Macro with Auto Drop<a name="50296"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 6 04 1:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>What someone told me once about *gasp* botting or *gasp* macroing foraging was that they would spend some time foraging whatever no drop items dropped in the zone they were foraging in, then forage an item or items they wanted to keep and put 1 in each free inventory slot.  What this did was allow them to forage the items they wanted and drop everything else.  The reason for making sure you already have 1 of each no drop item is so you can't forage any more of them and don't have to leave an empty slot for them that might get filled by other items you don't want.  Not sure if all that made sense, but there you go.</span></td>
