				<td colspan="2"><span>Well both answers point to a full inventory .. .I think,  The second answer was a bit hard to follow.. but I think I get the jist.  Now, even if you do have a full inventory, the foraged item ends up on your cursor.  Then you either drop or destroy.  But I am certain, well  kinda sure anyway, that I see rangers and druids macroing forage to train and drop items all over the ground automatically.  I suppose they might be just dropping via the little pop up window that says &quot;are you sure you want to drop this item on the ground&quot;.
<br />

<br />
And, as I said, you can turn &quot;fastitemdrop&quot; on, just like &quot;fastitemdestroy&quot; so you don't have to answer the pop up question.  But this can be dangerous.  Drop, not as much as destroy, but still if you drop somethign you didn't mean to and don't realize it, that would suck.
<br />

<br />
It's not that I'm lazy here.  I just wanted to train forage by mapping my forage button to my forward key.  But it can become a hassle if everytime you forage, it gets stuck on your cursor.. 
<br />

<br />
Oh well, guess I gotta just keep dropping on the ground via the pop up window... LOL
<br />

<br />
