				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Macro with Auto Drop<a name="50356"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 6 04 3:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One trick you can play to make sure you don't drop something valuable is to augment it, making it NO DROP.
<br />

<br />
With that in mind, you can make a social and bind it to your movement keys which does the following:
<br />

<br />
/doability 3   (or whatever your forage ability is)
<br />
/pause 5
<br />
/autoinv
<br />

<br />
The pause is needed because the forage has a bit of a delay to it, and if you don't put the pause in there, the /autoinv will fire off before you have anything on your cursor.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
