			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Macro with Auto Drop<a name="50371"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 6 04 4:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you fill all of your inventory slots with stacks of one item...that is, only one item instead of twenty, then any new items will just drop to the ground on hitting /autoinventory without triggering the confirmation box.  Sooo...say you have seven bags that are completely full and one empty 10 slot bag.  You go into a zone where you know two no drop items and the item you want(cinnamon sticks for instance) are on the forage table.  You forage until you have the two no drop items and 8 cinnamon sticks.  Instead of leaving the 8 sticks stacked, you put one in each of the remaining empty slots in the bag.  Now you can start the autoforage.  When you forage a cinnamon stick, it will go into the bag.  When you get one of the no drop items, (since they're usually lore as well) it just won't forage, won't even end up on the cursor.  When you forage anything besides cinnamon sticks it will just drop to the ground.  
<br />

<br />
Keep in mind, this is how the theory was explained to me and offhand I'm not sure if there are no drop foraged items that aren't lore as well...if there are, they would throw a wrench in the whole works.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=805235">Bhill Diekatze</a>, 65th, Terris Thule<br>
By a knight of ghosts and shadows I summoned am to tourney<br> 
